The directors for the Society of Antiquaries of London were important figures that oversaw the creation of plates for the volumes of Vetusta Monumenta. The plates within Volume 2 were overseen by four different directors. Here, the plates are organized by the director and the year of creation. John Fenn, a member of the society, would later classify most plates in Volume 2 using seven different categories. We classified the remaining plates. The specific classification for each plate is provided in the coinciding year.
